|}

Indicators <code>0x08</code>–<code>0x10</code> and <code>0x18</code>–<code>0xFD</code> are reserved for future dictionary entries.

=====Explicit path encoding=====

When the path encoding indicator is <code>0xFE</code>, the path is encoded explicitly:

# A LEB128-encoded unsigned integer giving the number of path components.
# For each path component: a LEB128-encoded child number, where hardened components encode <code>2c + 1</code> for child index <code>c</code> and unhardened components encode <code>2c</code>.

This convention follows the path encoding used by <code>descriptor-codec</code>.

